Holly Barber woke up feeling unwell and with chest and neck pains but thought it was just a bad hangover . 
  She started coughing up blood and was having difficulty breathing so rushed to hospital . 
  Doctors found she had 13 pulmonary embolisms - blood clots blocking the arteries in her lungs . 
  She was horrified to be told she was days from death . 
  A year later she was diagnosed with a melon-sized blockage in her right lung . 
  She had been drinking heavily and thought the problem was a hangover from heavy drinking . 
  Ms Barber believed she was suffering from a 'bad hangover' She was told the clots were blocking the main artery of her lungs and could kill her . 
 